SCHEDULE A
ALL THAT CERTAIN FARM OF LAND situate in the Town of Sharon, Schoharie County,
New York, bounded and described as follows: Said farm is bounded on the North by
lands of George U. Clausen; on the East by lands of Herbert Vrooman; on the South by
lands formerly of Lester Vrooman and Jacob Somers [Fromerly Irving Vrooman, Jacob J.
Banta and Emmett Collins] and on the West by lands of Jacob Somers, containing eighty
four [84] acres of land more or less, being the same premises conveyed to Burton
Vrooman by Jacob J. Banta et al by deed recorded in County Clerk's Office June 7, 1906
in Book 144 of Deeds at Page 67.
EXCEPTING and RESERVING out of and from the above described premises all that
certain tract or parcel of lands situate, lying and being in the Town of Sharon, Schoharie
County, New York, briefly described as follows: Commencing at a point in the center of
the highway, known as New York State Route No. 10 where the division line of the lands
hereby conveyed and the lands owned by Herbert Vrooman, one of the parties of the
second part join; thence continuing in an Easterly direction along said division line to the
Southeast corner of the lands hereby conveyed; thence in a Northerly direction along the
division line of the lands hereby conveyed and the lands of Herbert Vrooman and George
U. Clausen to the Northeasterly corner of the lands hereby conveyed; thence continuing
in a Westerly direction along the division line of the lands hereby conveyed and George
U. Clausen to the Northwesterly corner of the lands hereby conveyed; thence continuing
in a southerly direction along the line of the lands hereby conveyed and the lands of
Jacob Somers to the Southeasterly corner of the said Somer's lands; thence continuing
in a westerly direction along the division line of the land hereby conveyed and the lands
of Jacob Somers to the center of New York State Route 10; thence continuing in a
Southerly direction along center of said New York State 10 to the point or place of
beginning, containing about 60 acres of land be the same more or less.
